comment:
I had an old high school friend who lives in Alberta, Canada (Canada's "Texas"), and she was a perfectly normal person on her social media who worked as a pharmacist.  She was a healthcare worker (Well, I guess she probably still is) and lived a very normal appearing life for decades.

When Trump got into office, and later in the last couple of years when the whole "Convoy" debacle happened in Canada here, her social media SWIFTLY and SHARPLY changed.  All her photos started showing her wearing SO much more makeup than she used to (The kind of makeup job you see on people like Tammy Fae Baker, and religious fundamentalists), she started wearing cowboy hats, and every post she put on her page wall was some whacked out conspiracy theory about the government coming after your savings, about some vast imaginary wave of Canadians that were fleeing to the safe haven of Florida to escape the 'rising fascism' in Canada..... she went full on bonkers.

She wept in posts on her wall about how her own family had cut her off, and boasted about how she would never cut ties with anyone over a difference of opinions.  She saw herself as the more a virtuous person in that way...

I sat there, looking at month after month of insanity that she would post, until one day when she made a new post, citing her confusion over something or other (I can't remember at this point what it even was).  In the post she made an active call for someone to explain it to her, if she was wrong, she wanted someone to prove it...... so normally while I would never jump on someone else's wall uninvited just to 'fact check'.... she 'did' put out an open invite to do so.

I wrote one of the most eloquent pieces that I have ever conceived, and backed every point up with links to data, on government, and other official websites, that backed up every point I made.  She never responded to me, and the next day she disappeared from my friend's list.

 These people can't be helped, and they alays turn out to be the exact person that they are accusing other people of becoming.  It's sad that instead of decades of friendship, the only ay I ill ever see her now, is "that lunatic who was crying that she may have to sell her house and move to Florida because Canada was 'over'...".  I feel sorry for her husband and kids.  I blame the bubble of people she surrounded herself with.
